<div><ol><li>For a thundercloud at height&nbsp;\(d\), energy&nbsp;\(=\frac{1}{2}QEd\)</li><li>For a thundercloud at a new height&nbsp;\(d'\), energy&nbsp;\(=\frac{1}{2}QEd'\)</li><li>Because the <b>electric field strength is unchanged</b>, the increase inenergy stored is\[\frac{1}{2}QEd'-\frac{1}{2}QEd=\frac{1}{2}QE\Delta d\]where&nbsp;\(\Delta d=d'-d\)</li></ol></div>